The paper discusses the use of neural language models for generating image descriptions, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also explores different neural architectures for including visual information, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses transfer learning, which is a technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
